{
  "texts": [
    "While our approach improves multi-hop retrieval quality, it has several limitations that warrant further attention.",
    "Single-hop and adverse cases.",
    "Question decomposition can be counterproductive when the original query is already specific.",
    "In such cases, subqueries may introduce noise or distract from the original intent.",
    "In rare instances, none of the generated subqueries retrieve stronger evidence than the original query alone."
  ]
}